- [ ] Update dependencies: Semantic UI 2.4.1 is outdated
- [ ] Lazy load images: implement native loading="lazy"
- [ ] Consolidate fonts: 4 Google Fonts is excessive

Priority 4 (Low - Phase 4):
- [ ] Minify assets: unminified CSS/JS files (optional)
- [ ] Consider modern formats: WebP images with fallbacks (optional)

=== DEPENDENCIES ===

Current (Runtime):
- Semantic UI 2.4.1 (CSS framework) - CDN
- Font Awesome 4.7.0 (icons) - CDN
- jQuery (multiple versions, needs consolidation)
- Google Fonts (Roboto, Open Sans, Noto Sans, Merriweather Sans) - CDN
- Facebook SDK (social media integration)
- FullCalendar 6.1.9 (events page only)

Proposed Changes:
- Keep Semantic UI for now (consider removal in future)
- Update to Font Awesome 6.x or use CSS-only icons
- Consolidate to single jQuery version or remove
- Reduce to 1-2 Google Fonts
- Keep Facebook SDK and FullCalendar

Development Tools (Phase 4, optional):
- Image optimization: Sharp, Squoosh, or TinyPNG (manual)
- Code formatting: Prettier (optional, local only)
- Linting: ESLint, Stylelint (optional, local only)

Decision: Keep dependencies minimal. No npm/build process for deployment.
All dev tools are local/optional for code quality only.

